@startuml
' @id(CMP-INIT-CLI)
' @desc(CMP-INIT-CLI, "The `mdd init [--force]` subcommand in crates/mdd-cli/src/main.rs: the Commands::Init { force: bool } variant (a `--force` flag, mirroring `mdd clean --force`) and its match arm. The arm chooses the conflict handler — an always-Overwrite closure when force is set, otherwise the existing interactive prompt_init_conflict — and calls Project::init_with_conflict_handler. It then prints the InitReport, now including a `migrated {path}` line beside created/overwritten/skipped. Thin presentation layer, like Commands::Validate; the file-policy and migration logic live in CMP-INIT-ENGINE.")
' @id(CMP-INIT-ENGINE)
' @desc(CMP-INIT-ENGINE, "Project::init_with_conflict_handler in crates/mdd-core/src/lib.rs and its write helpers. It creates the directory tree, writes each REGENERABLE file through write_text_if_missing(handler) (so the handler decides overwrite vs skip on conflict), refreshes the CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md managed blocks, and invokes the SessionStart hook merge (CMP-INIT-HOOK). For the three AccumulatingState files it now calls write_yaml_create_or_migrate instead of write_yaml_create_only: create-from-default when missing, else a forward-only round-trip migration (DOM-STATE-MIGRATION) when the on-disk version is older, else skip. The state path never receives the conflict handler, so --force cannot reach config/trace/approvals. Returns InitReport { created, overwritten, migrated, skipped }.")
' Objective ownership for cycle 0018. The CLI adds a --force flag and a
' migrated report line; mdd-core gains create-or-migrate for state files
' while reusing its existing regenerable-file and hook machinery.
title MDD init — ownership (objective)

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev

component "mdd init [--force]\n(CMP-INIT-CLI)\nmdd-cli/src/main.rs" as Cli
component "Project::init_with_conflict_handler\n(CMP-INIT-ENGINE)\nmdd-core/src/lib.rs" as Engine
component "write_text_if_missing\n(regenerable: docs, skills, blocks)" as Text
component "write_yaml_create_or_migrate\n(state: config/trace/approvals)" as Yaml
component "SessionStart hook merge\n(CMP-INIT-HOOK)" as Hook

Dev --> Cli : mdd init [--force]
Cli --> Engine : init_with_conflict_handler(handler)
Cli --> Cli : handler = force ? always Overwrite : prompt
Engine --> Text : regenerable files (handler decides overwrite/skip)
Engine --> Yaml : state files (create or forward-migrate)
Engine --> Hook : upsert SessionStart hook (idempotent)

note bottom of Yaml
  Never consulted with the conflict handler, so --force
  cannot overwrite config/trace/approvals. Create when
  missing; round-trip migrate when on-disk version is
  older; skip when equal or newer. Reports `migrated`.
end note
@enduml
